Duck typing can be a useful tool in TypeScript, but it's important to use it judiciously. Overusing duck typing can lead to code that's harder to understand and maintain, as it can make it more difficult to track down type-related errors. It's generally best to use static typing as much as possible and only resort to duck typing when necessary.

